\subsection{Hybrid-Decoupled CAS}
\label{suD}
In this case, we propose an interference-aware optimization problem with an objective to achieve resource usage efficiency. An effective and controllable resource utilization on top of an interference-aware method may well entail in balanced interference mitigation and resource efficiency impact. The Disjoint-Decoupled approach might be optimal in terms of interference but it is not efficient in terms of resource usage. On the other hand, the Joint-Decoupled approach is optimal in the sense of resource usage but lacks of satisfactory interference performance compared to the two methods mentioned above. Hence, the Hybrid-Decoupled problem tries to strike the balance between interference and resource utilization.  

In order to realize this hybrid problem, an additional decision variable needs to be defined that will act as an indication of joint association for two devices that construct a D2D pair. This can be written as follows

